---
const pains = [
  "Can't tell if you're playing the right notes",
  "No feedback between lessons",
  "Generic courses that don't fit your level",
];
---

<section class="bg-background px-6 py-24 sm:px-10">
  <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-300 items-center gap-12 lg:grid-cols-2">
    <div class="rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-white/5 p-8 backdrop-blur-md">
      <div class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-secondary">
        Practicing alone is hard
      </div>
      <ul class="mt-6 space-y-4">
        {pains.map((pain) => (
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-secondary">
            <span class="mt-1 text-accent-amber">✕</span>
            <span>{pain}</span>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div>
      <div
        class="inline-block rounded-full border border-accent-cyan/40 bg-accent-cyan/5 px-4 py-1.5 text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-accent-cyan backdrop-blur-md"
      >
        The PianoAi Way
      </div>
      <h2
        class="mt-5 text-[clamp(1.75rem,5vw,2.75rem)] font-extrabold leading-tight tracking-tight bg-linear-to-br from-white via-[#a78bfa] to-accent-cyan bg-clip-text text-transparent"
      >
        PianoAi listens, corrects, and adapts in real time.
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-secondary">
        Every time you play, our AI hears what you hear — catching wrong
        notes, timing slips, and tempo issues, then adjusting your practice
        plan so you always know exactly what to work on next.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
